<Link id="l00088" /><CodeLine lineNumber="88"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">struct</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvmmcjitcompileroptions">LLVMMCJITCompilerOptions</a> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/debuginfo/lib/debuginfo/logicalview/lib/debuginfo/logicalview/core/lvoptions-cpp/#ab4088b7a11f3cbc38ac16a6e9c72494e">Options</a>, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">size&#95;t</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> SizeOfOptions);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00089" /><CodeLine lineNumber="89"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00090" /><CodeLine lineNumber="90"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42;&#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00091" /><CodeLine lineNumber="91"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; Create an MCJIT execution engine for a module, with the given options. It is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00092" /><CodeLine lineNumber="92"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; the responsibility of the caller to ensure that all fields in Options up to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00093" /><CodeLine lineNumber="93"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; the given SizeOfOptions are initialized. It is correct to pass a smaller</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00094" /><CodeLine lineNumber="94"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; value of SizeOfOptions that omits some fields. The canonical way of using</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00095" /><CodeLine lineNumber="95"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; this is:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00096" /><CodeLine lineNumber="96"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00097" /><CodeLine lineNumber="97"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; LLVMMCJITCompilerOptions options;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00098" /><CodeLine lineNumber="98"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; LLVMInitializeMCJITCompilerOptions(&amp;options, sizeof(options));</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00099" /><CodeLine lineNumber="99"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; ... fill in those options you care about</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00100" /><CodeLine lineNumber="100"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; LLVMCreateMCJITCompilerForModule(&amp;jit, mod, &amp;options, sizeof(options),</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00101" /><CodeLine lineNumber="101"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;                                  &amp;error);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00102" /><CodeLine lineNumber="102"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00103" /><CodeLine lineNumber="103"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; Note that this is also correct, though possibly suboptimal:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00104" /><CodeLine lineNumber="104"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00105" /><CodeLine lineNumber="105"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; LLVMCreateMCJITCompilerForModule(&amp;jit, mod, 0, 0, &amp;error);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00106" /><CodeLine lineNumber="106"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00107" /><CodeLine lineNumber="107"><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/groups/llvmcsupporttypes/#ga209de0bceb13179a973c6a45211617bd">LLVMBool</a> <a href="/docs/api/groups/llvmcexecutionengine/#gaa97dff3ed910ce2e0fc7c96b50b1c897">LLVMCreateMCJITCompilerForModule</a>(</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00177" /><CodeLine lineNumber="177"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; @param FinalizeMemory Set page permissions and flush cache. Return 0 on</span></CodeLine>
